description.plain: Bilmuri (pronounced exactly like the actor Bill Murray) is the latest musical outlet of Johnny Franck, formerly of Attack Attack!. Since 2016, the post-hardcore band has released 9 albums.

Johnny said this about the song:
“When you get hurt by people, it’s easy to just completely close yourself off to people…Well this C.S. Lewis quote says it best -

‘To love at all is to be vulnerable. Love anything and your heart will be wrung and possibly broken. If you want to make sure of keeping it intact you must give it to no one, not even an animal. Wrap it carefully round with hobbies and little luxuries; avoid all entanglements. Lock it up safe in the casket or coffin of your selfishness. But in that casket, safe, dark, motionless, airless, it will change. It will not be broken; it will become unbreakable, impenetrable, irredeemable. To love is to be vulnerable.’

It’s always tempting to close yourself off to people but it’s a miserable life."

description.plain: “THICC THICCLY” is about being there for a loved one. The lead single from Bilmuri’s RICH SIPS features Caleb Shomo, who used to be a part of Ohio based metalcore band Attack Attack! along with Johnny Franck. The song title references “Stick Stickly”, an iconic Attack Attack! track that influenced many metalcore bands who came out around 2009.

description.plain:
“melancholy” is the first single and opening track off Bilmuri’s seventh album Taco, which came out three months before the album’s release with a looping music video.

The song is about being depressed over feeling alone and unnoticed, picking up unhealthy habits, making him go insane and cry out for help.

description.plain:
“lvl70champion” is the last track off Bilmuri’s seventh album Taco. The song was supposed to be titled “Stick Stickly Pt. 2” in reference to his former band’s track “Stick Stickly,” but in the end it had to be changed due to distribution reasons.

The track is about seeking a purpose in life and finding hope in others when you feel the world’s against you.

description.plain: “SOURDOUGHSTARTER” is the last track in Bilmuri’s ninth album RICH SIPS, standing out as the most romantic song in the record. This is another collab between Bilmuri and No Dice, the first one being their shared EP DiceMuri, which featured covers of “Slow Dancing In The Dark,” “Sunflower,” I Always Wanna Die (Sometimes) and “when the party’s over.”

body.plain: Bilmuri (pronounced exactly like the actor Bill Murray) is the latest musical outlet of Johnny Franck, formerly of Attack Attack!. Since 2016, the post-hardcore band has released 9 albums.
